Unfortunately, the concept of deterring someone who is *INTENDING* to die is somewhat poorly thought out.  If nothing else, you may encourage them.  Now, there is no thought of smuggling weapons, only of being able to take the one that is already available.  Against someone who wants to live, and actively fears death, it may work as a superb deterrant.  But against someone who has resigned themselves to die, it will probably have very little effect.  See movie &quot;Ghost Dog&quot;, see &quot;A Book of Five Rings&quot;, see any location in the world with suicide bombers.  <br>
<br>
Not having a gun on board, having a gun on board; both have pros and cons.  I am of a very mixed mind on the subject.  I suspect it will ultimately end up being a non-issue.  I doubt there will be any attempts similar to 9/11.  After all; the big thing to do now is to top it, not repeat it.  And that is far scarier than a gun on a plane.<br>
<br>
